EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 312300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO BE LOCATED S OF ICELAND
WHILST HIGH PRESSURE LIES TO THE S OF THE UK ACROSS FRANCE. OVERNIGHT THE
HIGH IS EXP TO DECLINE EWARDS INTO SE EUROPE AS THE LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM RPDY
DEEPENS AND MOVS INTO SE ICELAND. THE LOW IS THEN FCST TO CONTINUE ITS SLOW
EWARDS PROGRESS INTO THE NORWEGIAN BASIN FOR FRIDAY AND SCANDINAVIA ON SATURDAY
GRADUALLY FLN AS IT DOES. MEANWHILE HIGH PRESSURE IN THE MID-ATLANTIC IS
EXP TO TRANSFER EWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED OVER FRANCE BY THE END OF THE PERIOD.
ON WEDNESDAY NIGHT STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE EXP TO SPREAD E ACROSS
THE N OF CULLERCOATS. THESE EXTENDING SWARDS THROUGH THURSDAY TO AFFECT MUCH
OF THE REGION FOR THE REST OF THE PERIOD. OCCASIONAL GALES ARE LIKELY ACROSS
THE N CULLERCOATS FM THURSDAY NIGHT UNTIL SATURDAY MORNING
